main event: A civilian man observed a bright object over the Mississippi River on November 11, 1952.
interesting points: The object was seen at a height of 5 to 10 miles.,The sighting occurred at 11:45 PM CST.,The object rose quickly from 12 degrees above the horizon to 22 degrees in 2 seconds.,About 3 minutes later, a twin-engine aircraft approached from the east.,The weather was clear, allowing visibility of more than 15 miles.
sighted object: a bright object in the sky
